radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is dilated and does not fill with enteric contrast, measuring approximately 14 mm in diameter. No evidence of perforation. Adnexal lesion contains fat and soft tissue elements as well as calcified material measuring approximately 3.7 x 4.2 x 4.0 cm, compatible with a right ovarian dermoid. Clear lung bases. Normal liver, gallbladder, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, and urinary bladder.
